(Assignment 4 technical description) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Purpose of the repository) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This repository is the Assignment 4 version of the thesis project. The point of this stage) Tj
T*
(is not to present final scientific results yet, but to put the work into a form that is easy) Tj
T*
(to run, inspect, and repeat.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The thesis question stays the same as in Assignment 3: whether demographic structure helps) Tj
T*
(explain variation in hospital service use across GP practices in Scotland beyond a simpler) Tj
T*
(baseline based on practice size and GP availability. What changes here is the technical) Tj
T*
(setup around that question. Instead of relying on loose scripts or notebook-only work, the) Tj
T*
(project is organized as a small pipeline with documented inputs, configuration files, and) Tj
T*
(saved outputs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In practical terms, another person should be able to see where raw data belongs, run the) Tj
T*
(main commands from the repository root, and identify which configuration produced a given) Tj
T*
(model and a given metrics file.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Repository layout) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project is split into a few clear areas:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- data/raw/ for source files,) Tj
T*
(- data/processed/ for datasets created by preprocessing,) Tj
T*
(- config/ for shared settings and experiment definitions,) Tj
T*
(- src/ for the actual implementation,) Tj
T*
(- reports/ for metrics and run metadata,) Tj
T*
(- models/ for saved estimators,) Tj
T*
(- docs/ for the written documentation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Inside src/, the responsibilities are separated instead of mixed into one script.) Tj
T*
(data_pipeline.py handles reading and shaping the input data. modeling.py builds the scikit-) Tj
T*
(learn pipeline and calculates metrics. tracking.py is responsible for where results are) Tj
T*
(written. The command files preprocess.py, train.py, and evaluate.py are thin wrappers around) Tj
T*
(those reusable modules.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project also uses one consistent command style:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(text) Tj
T*
(python -m src <command> --config <file>) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That keeps execution predictable. It also makes the README and the reproducibility protocol) Tj
T*
(shorter, because all main actions follow the same pattern.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Data flow and preprocessing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(At the moment the pipeline expects one raw workbook in data/raw/:) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
