(- gp_practice_population_demographics_merged.xlsx) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The preprocessing code reads the data sheet, checks that the required columns exist, parses) Tj
T*
(the Date column, and reshapes the workbook into an analytical table with one row per) Tj
T*
(practice and date.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The demographic derivation is straightforward. Rows with Sex == "All" provide total) Tj
T*
(population and the age-band counts. Rows with Sex == "Female" are merged back in so the) Tj
T*
(pipeline can calculate share_female. From those values the code derives the main demographic) Tj
T*
(ratios used later in the experiments:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- share_age_0_14) Tj
T*
(- share_age_65_plus) Tj
T*
(- share_female) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current repository does not yet ship the real hospital outcome table, GP workforce data,) Tj
T*
(or deprivation controls. Because of that, src/data_pipeline.py creates placeholder columns) Tj
T*
(for:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- gp_availability) Tj
T*
(- deprivation_index) Tj
T*
(- hospital_use_per_1000) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These placeholders are deterministic, so they let the full project run in a repeatable way,) Tj
T*
(but they are not meant to be treated as real thesis data. The generated manifest in) Tj
T*
(data/processed/ records that these variables were created as stand-ins. This is important) Tj
T*
(because it makes the limitation explicit instead of hiding it.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Configuration and experiment setup) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository uses YAML files to separate implementation from experiment definition.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(config/base.yaml contains the shared settings: paths, Python version, random seed,) Tj
T*
(preprocessing defaults, output locations, and tracking settings. The experiment files extend) Tj
T*
(that base file and only override what differs between runs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The current experiments are:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- experiment_f0.yaml - baseline feature set, using AllAges and gp_availability, trained with) Tj
T*
(OLS) Tj
T*
(- experiment_f1.yaml - extended feature set, adding share_age_65_plus, share_female,) Tj
T*
(deprivation_index, and categorical controls HB and HSCP, trained with Ridge regression) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This arrangement matters for two reasons. First, switching from one experiment to another) Tj
T*
(does not require code changes. Second, the exact merged configuration can be saved next to) Tj
T*
(the results, which makes later inspection much easier.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Training and evaluation logic) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The training path is implemented in src/modeling.py. It builds a scikit-learn pipeline with) Tj
ET
