(separate handling for numeric and categorical features.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For numeric columns, the pipeline applies median imputation and, if enabled, standard) Tj
T*
(scaling. For categorical columns, it applies most-frequent imputation followed by one-hot) Tj
T*
(encoding. The final estimator is chosen from the config and is currently either OLS or) Tj
T*
(Ridge.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The evaluation logic mirrors the plan from Assignment 3:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- 80/20 hold-out split) Tj
T*
(- 5-fold cross-validation) Tj
T*
(- metrics: R2, RMSE, and MAE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The code stores both hold-out and cross-validation summaries in metrics.json, together with) Tj
T*
(the feature lists and a small prediction preview. The evaluate command does not retrain the) Tj
T*
(model. It reads the stored artifacts for the deterministic run folder that matches the given) Tj
T*
(config.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Traceability and reproducibility) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository uses a few simple rules to keep runs traceable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(First, the environment is pinned with requirements.txt and environment.yml, and the) Tj
T*
(documented Python version is 3.11.9. Second, the seed is stored in configuration and is) Tj
T*
(applied before training. Third, the project resolves paths relative to the repository root,) Tj
T*
(so it does not depend on machine-specific absolute paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The most visible traceability mechanism is the run folder name. It is derived from the) Tj
T*
(experiment name, configuration hash, and seed. As long as those inputs stay the same, the) Tj
T*
(run slug stays the same as well.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Each training run writes:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- reports/runs/<run_slug>/metrics.json) Tj
T*
(- reports/runs/<run_slug>/metadata.json) Tj
T*
(- reports/runs/<run_slug>/config_snapshot.yaml) Tj
T*
(- models/<run_slug>/model.joblib) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In addition, reports/experiment_registry.json keeps a top-level index of the saved runs. The) Tj
T*
(metadata includes the processed dataset hash, the git commit hash, and environment details.) Tj
T*
(That gives a direct link between reported numbers and the code state that produced them.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Current limitations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main limitation of the current repository is data availability, not code structure. The) Tj
T*
(pipeline is ready to accept the real hospital outcome, workforce, and deprivation sources,) Tj
T*
(but those tables are not part of the shared package yet.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When those data sources are available, the placeholder generation in preprocessing should be) Tj
T*
(removed and replaced with the real merge logic. The rest of the project layout can stay the) Tj
ET
endstream
